00:09:13.380 --> 00:09:17.660
The reason for talking about the law
at an accessibility conference

00:09:17.780 --> 00:09:20.180
is because accessibility
is a legal right.

00:09:20.580 --> 00:09:23.660
I use the word civil right
in the title of this talk,

00:09:23.780 --> 00:09:25.260
and as I was preparing it,

00:09:25.700 --> 00:09:29.740
I was thinking, "What actually
is the difference between a human right

00:09:29.860 --> 00:09:30.540
and a civil right?"

00:09:30.660 --> 00:09:32.820
In the US, we tend to talk about civil rights.

00:09:32.980 --> 00:09:37.060
I've seen around the world
and with global treaties,

00:09:37.180 --> 00:09:38.540
they tend to talk about human rights.

00:09:39.020 --> 00:09:41.900
Something I probably
should have known a long time ago,

00:09:41.980 --> 00:09:43.420
and many of you probably do know,

00:09:43.580 --> 00:09:47.460
human rights are the rights
we acquire by being alive.

00:09:47.620 --> 00:09:51.140
Things that should be
our inherent right as people.

00:09:51.340 --> 00:09:55.340
Civil rights are those
that we get from laws where we live.

00:09:55.460 --> 00:09:58.860
Civil rights might be different
in different places,

00:09:58.980 --> 00:10:03.860
but human rights are everywhere,
and digital accessibility is both.

00:10:04.300 --> 00:10:06.060
It's both a human right and a civil right

00:10:06.180 --> 00:10:10.060
because it's about participation.

00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:15.340
Think of anything you do,
anything you're working on,

00:10:15.420 --> 00:10:16.660
whatever sector you're in.

00:10:17.180 --> 00:10:21.420
If you're on accessibility,
you're on to helping people participate.

00:10:21.580 --> 00:10:23.900
It's about inclusion,
not exclusion,

00:10:24.060 --> 00:10:27.100
which is why I have the exclusion
double struck out on the slide.

00:10:27.260 --> 00:10:28.700
It's about communication.

00:10:28.860 --> 00:10:29.980
It's about education.

00:10:30.180 --> 00:10:31.660
It's about health and safety.

00:10:31.780 --> 00:10:35.100
Just think what's going on in Florida
and the United States right now,

00:10:35.220 --> 00:10:38.420
bracing for another terrible climate crisis hurricane,

00:10:38.620 --> 00:10:42.220
so much information spread out
on the internet.

00:10:42.420 --> 00:10:47.340
Digital without accessibility,
it's a risk to disabled people.

00:10:47.500 --> 00:10:50.100
That's just one example, and so much more.

