00:21:37.140 --> 00:21:41.020
which is to illustrate the fact
that the Department of Justice and Health

00:21:41.100 --> 00:21:44.660
and Human Services,
they have really good guidance on telehealth

00:21:44.780 --> 00:21:47.780
and how that needs
to be accessible and health care in general.

00:21:47.940 --> 00:21:50.540
The DOJ and the EEOC,

00:21:50.700 --> 00:21:55.740
which is the Employment Federal Agency
Equal Employment Opportunity Commission,

00:21:55.900 --> 00:21:59.540
they have a really great guidance
on AI hiring tools

00:21:59.700 --> 00:22:04.620
and the risk
to disabled people if disability rights

00:22:04.820 --> 00:22:08.660
and civil rights aren't considered
when using AI hiring tools.

00:22:08.820 --> 00:22:13.220
President Biden has issued executive orders
on AI that include disability.

00:22:13.340 --> 00:22:16.460
The Department of Education,
Department of Justice,

00:22:16.580 --> 00:22:19.780
have what they call
a Dear Colleague letter, which is guidance,

00:22:19.940 --> 00:22:21.580
I don't know why they call it that.

00:22:21.660 --> 00:22:23.660
I don't think anyone else
in the federal government does,

00:22:23.820 --> 00:22:27.540
but it's all about
the importance of accessibility,

00:22:27.700 --> 00:22:31.580
digital inclusion for disabled people
in the higher ed space.

00:22:31.700 --> 00:22:36.140
I have articles on all these things,

00:22:36.300 --> 00:22:41.020
